title: Warwickshire baby girl is born with two front TEETH
text: Share 202 shares Miss Lines said: 'I was completely delirious with all the morphine and other painkillers. Suddenly a midwife said my baby had two front teeth. It was a complete surprise. 'Everyone was telling me how amazing it was that my baby had front teeth, but I had very little idea of how rare that is. Proud: Samantha and her partner Jason Coombs, pictured in hospital, struggled to conceive Be careful! Mother Samantha, right with Ella-Rose, admitted she was nervous to breastfeed Lucky baby: Tiny Ella-Rose looks cute in a pink bow as she gurgles happily for the camera 'It wasn't until I came to and somebody told me that it actually sunk in that this was such a unique thing. The doctors have told me that it's very rare for this to happen.' Bar manager Miss Lines said she has also been warned over the potential dangers of the baby teeth. 'I've been told that I have to keep an eye on the teeth in case they fall because they could be a choking hazard,' she said. Risks: Samantha has been warned her daughter's teeth, pictured, could be a choking hazard 'I'm not even sure whether or not I should be brushing them or not. They look very delicate, so I don't know whether I should even be touching them at all.' The new mother has turned to Google for advice but said there is very information as it is such a rare occurrence. She added: 'It's just something extra to deal with on top of everything else. You're trying to learn everything when you're a new mum, but I need more guidance.' Share or comment on this article 202
